HEADWORD: Cyclopedic
<hw>Cy`clo*ped"ic</hw> <pr>(s?`kl?-p?d"?k ⟦or⟧ -p?"d?k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Belonging to the circle of the sciences, or to a
cyclopedia; of the nature of a cyclopedia; hence, of great range,
extent, or amount; <as>as, a man of <ex>cyclopedic</ex>
knowledge</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cyclopedist</ent>⟦br⟧
